citation.title: Protogynous hermaphroditism in a temperate reef fish, the blackeye goby, Coryphopterus nicholsii (Pisces: Gobiidae)

facebook.title: Timeline Photos
facebook.summary: Blackeyed and gender-bending beauty! Blackeye Goby amid Short Plumose Anemones. The species starts of female and switches to become a male under the right conditions (protogynous hermaphrodism). The theory is that the females become males when they are big
